.TH "drm_is_current_master" 9 "drm_is_current_master" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_is_current_master \- checks whether @priv is the current master
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_is_current_master
.BI "(struct drm_file *fpriv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fpriv" 12
DRM file private
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether \fIfpriv\fP is current master on its device. This decides whether a
client is allowed to run DRM_MASTER IOCTLs.

Most of the modern IOCTL which require DRM_MASTER are for kernel modesetting
- the current master is assumed to own the non-shareable display hardware.
